node.text:
The fine folks at @lastdropbeerfestival featured our Dole Whip-inspired smoothie-style berliner in their festival last Saturday and shot some great footage in our new cellar space!

If you scored #TropicalHideaway cans out in their first shot at limited distribution today, give this clip a listen and make sure you’re storing those cans cold, drinking ‘em fresh, and giving them a proper tiki-shake before you open and pour! 

(Also, huge-huge-huge congrats to the Cast Members bringing #Disneyland back to life today! Come grab a draft beer at 20% off today [and everyday!] with your TWDC ID!)

🐢
🐢
🐢

node.title: Last Drop Beer Festival: Tropical Hideaway

node.text:
CAN DROP: #SupernaturalPerfectMatch - Hazy DIPA collaboration with @electricbrewingco • 8.5% ABV • Supernatural Perfect Match hits every Hazy DIPA bullseye -- tropical aromas of sweet pineapple and guava, bold flavors of succulent summer cantaloupe, and a finishing bite of candied orange peel bitterness all housed in a big, fluffy body with a silky hint of lactose. 

Cans go live at 11:45am for same-day, no-proxy pick-up by 10:00pm!

📱 • Order beer-to-go at the link in our profile!
🚗 • Pick up at #StageSelect from 12:00 - 10:00pm daily!⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⛱ • Enjoy on-premise service indoors & outdoors!
🍔 • @hammer.burger joins us at 5:00pm, bring a lunch before then!

Fellow Innovators! It’s the proxy-friendly Eventbrite sale day for #BrokenBlender2021!

Notes of orange zest and nutmeg garnish aromatic waves of dark rum and tropical fruit, setting the tone for this Painkiller cocktail-inspired imperial stout.

After eighteen months in Jamaican rum barrels, #BrokenBlender was pushed through three unique rounds of 300lbs of fresh coconut. The full-bodied sweetness of a cumulative 900lbs of coconut was tempered with 400lbs of sliced pineapple pieces for a vibrant tropical tang, then finished with a twist of orange zest and a dash of nutmeg.
⁣⁣
=============== SALE DETAILS ===============⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• Tickets go live at the top link in our profile at 12:00pm, limit 4pp.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
• If you've already purchased bottles in our local-access direct sale, you're still welcome to participate in today's Eventbrite sale.⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
• Proxy pickup is welcome in our Eventbrite sales! ⁣⁣⁣⁣There is no limit on how many orders a person may retrieve as a proxy. Proxy registration takes place during the ticket registration, though you may edit details through the link in your confirmation email afterward.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• You will need the following information to register a proxy: Their Full Name, Date of Birth, and email address.⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣ Your proxy MUST show ID that matches these information fields to retrieve bottles.
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
=============== Pick Up Details =========⁣======⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• Bottles are immediately available for retrieval at the brewery from 7/25 - 8/8.
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣ ⁣
• Again, proxy pick-ups are permitted but must be registered through Eventbrite. You are able to adjust your proxy post-purchase through the link in your confirmation email. ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
• We strongly recommend picking up on weekdays from 6-10pm. Saturday/Sunday crowds are inevitable, avoid them as best you can! ⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣⁣

node.text:
Fellow Innovators! We're delighted to share the delicious details regarding the seventh annual release of #FundamentalObservation2021, our chart-topping Bourbon Barrel Aged Imperial Vanilla Stout:

#FundamentalObservation's original incarnation was honored as 2015's Best New Beer on @beeradvocate. It maintains two entries on @untappd's Top 50 rated beers for the 2016 and 2017 vintages and earned Gold in the Festival of Wood & Barrel-Aged Beers's Specialty Strong/Porter Stout category before going on to win @fobab's 2018's Best In Show.

For the last six releases, we firmly maintained an exact replica of the 100% single-mash stout base. As Fundamental Observation enters its seventh year, we're proud to push this legendary beer forward with a 75% to 25% ratio of double-mash to single-mash liquid for a rich, creamy mouthfeel and lingering velvety finish.

This "liquid brownie batter" was aged in a blend of Heaven Hill, Elijah Craig, and Willett bourbon barrels and finishes out at a mighty 14% ABV. Each barrel saw multiple additions of Madagascar vanilla beans, ultimately aging the finished batch of beer with hundreds of pounds of vanilla over the course of a year.

Madagascar's premier crop benefitted beautifully from extended vine-ripening time over the last year and the vanilla character in Fundamental Observation 2021 is unmistakably bold. Familiar flavors of cookie dough and baking chocolate envelope the palate with hints at brûléed sugar, all balanced with beautiful barrel tones and present-but-pleasant alcohol heat.
⁣⁣

Toast sales culminate at sell-through or at 10:00pm on Saturday 7/31; any remaining inventory will be sold in a proxy-friendly Eventbrite sale on 8/1.
